# Quality gates (run before committing)
- Run tests: `make test`
- Run linter: `make lint`
- Format code: `make fmt`
- Run all checks: `make check`

# Code style
- Follow the Go spec: docs/specs/language/go.md
- Use conventional commits: docs/specs/practices/conventional-commits.md
- Write tests first (TDD): docs/specs/practices/tdd.md

# Go-specific rules
- Use gofmt and goimports for formatting
- Run `go test -race` for concurrency safety
- Check errors at every call site
- Wrap errors with `fmt.Errorf("...: %w", err)`
- Pass context.Context as first parameter for I/O functions
- No panics in library code for expected failures

# Commit messages
- Follow conventional commits format
- Reference spec rules when applicable

# Agent-checkers specific rules
- Game engine (internal/app/) has no external dependencies (no HTTP, no DB)
- All moves must be validated through rules/validator.go
- Board coordinates: 0-indexed, row 0 is black's home row
- Red always moves first
- Captures are mandatory — if a jump is available, it must be taken
- All new features need corresponding BDD tests in tests/features/